der/indland/nyt-coronatilfaelde-er-en-medarbejder-paa-aarhus-universitetshospital | publisher=[[DR (broadcaster)|DR]] | language=Danish | trans-title=New corona case is a worker at Aahus university hospital | accessdate=29 February 2020 }}</ref> On 3 March, five people who had returned from Northern Italy tested positive.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Andreasen|first=Kasper B.|url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-03-femte-og-sjette-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus|title=Femte og sjette dansker smittet med coronavirus|date=3 March 2020|work=TV 2|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Hagemann-Nielsen|first=Frederik|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/sundhedsminister-mindst-10-herhjemme-er-nu-smittet-med-corona|title=Sundhedsminister: Mindst 10 herhjemme er nu smittet med corona|date=3 March 2020|work=DR|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Estonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Estonia confirmed its second case, a patient who had arrived on 29 February from Bergamo and was travelling through [[Riga Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Second case of coronavirus diagnosed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059432/second-case-of-coronavirus-diagnosed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=4 March 2020|date=3 March 2020 }}</ref> Two other Estonian passengers from the same flight and one returnee from Bergamo arriving through Tallinn Airport tested positive on 5 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=Third coronavirus case confirmed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059950/third-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kahel Bergamost naasnud tallinlasel tuvastati koroonaviirus |url=https://www.err.ee/1060498/kahel-bergamost-naasnud-tallinlasel-tuvastati-koroonaviirus |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020 |language=Estonian| trans-title=Two Tallinners returning from Bergamo infected with coronavirus|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref> T