.go.th/?url=pr/detail/2/04/139480 |script-title=th:\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e02\u0e48\u0e32\u0e27\u0e01\u0e23\u0e13\u0e35\u0e44\u0e27\u0e23\u0e31\u0e2a\u0e42\u0e04\u0e42\u0e23\u0e19\u0e32 2019 (COVID-19) \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e08\u0e33\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 5 \u0e21\u0e35\u0e19\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21 2563|trans-title=Report of COVID-19 situation in Thailand, 5 March 2020|language=Thai|via=[[Ministry of Public Health (Thailand)|Ministry of Public Health, Thailand]]|date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[United Arab Emirates]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, two Italian staff members of the [[UAE Tour]], a cycling event, tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cyclists await test results after coronavirus hits UAE Tour |url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/sports/1868344/cyclists-await-test-results-after-coronavirus-hits-uae-tour |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Bangkok Post |date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Vietnam]]''' \u2013\nCase 17 had travelled to Italy (as well as to France and the UK).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lepetitjournal.com/ho-chi-minh/actualites/covid-19-au-vietnam-un-17eme-cas-confirme-hanoi-275441|title=COVID-19 au Vietnam : un 17\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Hanoi|website=lepetitjournal.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Europe===\n\n'''[[Albania]]''' \u2013\nOn 9 March, a 54-year-old man and his 28-year-old son, who had travelled from Florence to Albania by car, were confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Konfirmohen dy rastet e para me koronavirusin e ri |url=http://shendetesia.gov.al/ministria-e-shendetesise-konfirmohen-dy-rastet-e-para-me-koronavirusin-e-ri/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |date=9 March 2020 |language=Albanian}}</ref> Three other people from the men's family were suspected of having the virus. Another Albanian who had gone to Italy for a one-day trip is suspected.\n\n'''[[Andorra]]''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Andorra registered its first case, a 20-year-old man who had been to Milan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Andorra r