onavirus-diagnosed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=4 March 2020|date=3 March 2020 }}</ref> Two other Estonian passengers from the same flight and one returnee from Bergamo arriving through Tallinn Airport tested positive on 5 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=Third coronavirus case confirmed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059950/third-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kahel Bergamost naasnud tallinlasel tuvastati koroonaviirus |url=https://www.err.ee/1060498/kahel-bergamost-naasnud-tallinlasel-tuvastati-koroonaviirus |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020 |language=Estonian| trans-title=Two Tallinners returning from Bergamo infected with coronavirus|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref> Two cases in [[Saaremaa]] were confirmed on 10 March: the patients had been in contact with the [[Power Volley Milano]] team members during the [[2019\u201320 CEV Challenge Cup]] matches held in Saaremaa on 4 and 5 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lisandus veel kolm koroonasse nakatunut |language=Estonian |trans-title=Three new corona cases |url= https://www.err.ee/1062388/lisandus-veel-kolm-koroonasse-nakatunut |publisher=ERR |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=17th person diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1062618/17th-person-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March 5 Milan players had been diagnosed with fever before a league match.<ref>{{cite news |title=Volley, febbre al termoscanner: Milano-Padova non si gioca |language=Italian |trans-title=Volleyball, thermoscanner fever: Milan-Padua is not played |url=https://sport.sky.it/volley/2020/03/08/coronavirus-volley-partita-sospesa-milano-padova |publisher=Sky Sport |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> The infected in Saaremaa included the CEO of the [[Saaremaa VK]] volleyball club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Koroonaviiruse saanud Saaremaa v\u00f5rkpa